The paper deals with statistical properties of dictionaries and their associated Gram matrices, which are common topics in information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SP), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of eigenvalue distributions is also a common tool in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and statistical physics (cs.SI).
